POLICE are currently dealing with an &quot;ongoing incident&quot; in the centre of Govan, Glasgow
Officers attended the scene at Shaw Street shortly after 4am this morning.
All approaches to the street have been closed off to the public.
A cordon has been thrown up around a stretch of Govan Road between Golspie Street and Burleigh Street.
A Police Scotland spokeswoman said: &quot;There is an ongoing police incident in Shaw Street but there is no further information available at this time.&quot;
